# Game code

- Put Babylon `Engine` / `Scene` setup only in `CornholeSceneService` (or future dedicated engine classes under `game/`). Do not create WebGL contexts from arbitrary components.
- Always dispose Babylon resources when the host component is destroyed (`dispose()` on the service).
- Scoring and round rules belong in `GameStateService`; the scene service should call into it only after physics settle, wrapped in `NgZone.run` when updating UI-facing state.
- Prefer `PhysicsImpostor` with Ammo (`AmmoJSPlugin`) for static colliders (mass 0) and the soft-body bag; avoid adding physics bodies outside the `game/` folder without a clear reason.
